---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.tsx";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const { href } = Astro.url;
---

<Layout title="About John Tsevdos" description="About John Tsevdos" url={href}>
  <Header client:load />

  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16 lg:px-8 xl:max-w-7xl">
    <header>
      <h1 class="mb-2 text-4xl font-black text-black dark:text-white">About üòÅ</h1>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-medium leading-relaxed mb-8 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Learn more about me</h2>
    </header>

    <article
      class="max-w-full prose prose-xl md:prose-2xl prose-a:text-blue-700 dark:prose-invert dark:prose-a:text-blue-400"
    >
      <p>
        I am a <strong>software engineer</strong> from <strong>Athens, Greece</strong> üá¨üá∑, with over <strong
          >18 years of experience</strong
        >
        crafting elegant and effective web applications. Currently, I work at <strong
          ><a class="font-bold" href="https://orfium.com" target="_blank">Orfium</a></strong
        > as a <strong>front-end team leader</strong> (Senior Software Engineer Level 2), a company specializing in music
        rights management and monetization solutions. Outside of work, I enjoy working on <strong
          ><a class="font-bold" href="/open-source-software" target="_blank">personal projects</a></strong
        >, contributing to <strong
          ><a class="font-bold" href="https://github.com/tsevdos" target="_blank">open-source projects</a></strong
        >, and consulting on web applications and technologies. I also share my knowledge of <strong>JavaScript</strong
        >, <strong>TypeScript</strong>, and <strong>React</strong> as an <strong> instructor</strong> at seminars and workshops,
        and I co-host the <strong
          ><a class="font-bold" href="https://www.meetup.com/react-to-react-athens-meetup/" target="_blank"
            >React Athens Meetup</a
          ></strong
        >.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the past <strong>8 years</strong>, I have been building <strong>web applications</strong> using <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://facebook.github.io/react/"
          target="_blank">React</a
        > and frameworks such as <a class="font-bold" href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank">Next.js</a>, <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://tanstack.com/start/latest"
          target="_blank">TanStack Start</a
        > and <a class="font-bold" href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank">Astro</a>. I have worked with a wide
        range of state management tools, from <a href="https://redux.js.org/" target="_blank">Redux</a> and
        <a href="https://mobx.js.org/" target="_blank">Mobx</a> to
        <a href="https://recoiljs.org/" target="_blank">Recoil</a>
        and <a href="https://zustand.surge.sh" target="_blank">Zustand</a>. I have also used many libraries from the
        <strong>React ecosystem</strong>, including <a
          href="https://github.com/ReactTraining/react-router"
          target="_blank">React Router</a
        >, <a href="https://react-query.tanstack.com/" target="_blank">React Query</a>, <a
          href="https://www.styled-components.com/"
          target="_blank">Styled-Components</a
        >, <a href="https://emotion.sh" target="_blank">emotion.js</a>, <a
          href="https://react-hook-form.com/"
          target="_blank">React Hook Form</a
        >, <a href="https://formatjs.io/" target="_blank">React i18n</a>, <a href="https://ant.design/" target="_blank"
          >Ant Design</a
        >, <a href="https://material-ui.com/" target="_blank">Material UI</a>, <a
          href="https://reactstrap.github.io/"
          target="_blank">Reactstrap</a
        >, and more. I continuously strive to improve my skills by learning <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://go.dev/"
          target="_blank">Go</a
        > and exploring functional and reactive programming with languages and libraries like <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://gleam.run/"
          target="_blank">Gleam</a
        >, <a href="http://ramdajs.com/" target="_blank">Ramda.js</a>, and <a
          href="http://reactivex.io/rxjs/"
          target="_blank">RxJS</a
        >. Additionally, I have hands-on experience with other <strong>JavaScript frameworks and libraries</strong> such
        as <a href="https://vuejs.org/" target="_blank">Vue.js</a>, <a href="https://angular.io/" target="_blank"
          >Angular</a
        >, <a href="https://svelte.dev" target="_blank">Svelte</a>, <a href="http://backbonejs.org/" target="_blank"
          >Backbone.js</a
        >, <a href="https://jquery.com/" target="_blank">jQuery</a>, <a href="http://underscorejs.org/" target="_blank"
          >Underscore</a
        >, <a href="https://lodash.com/" target="_blank">lodash</a>, <a
          href="https://github.com/mzabriskie/axios"
          target="_blank">axios</a
        >, <a href="https://date-fns.org/" target="_blank">date-fns</a>, and many more.
      </p>
      <p>
        On the <strong>backend stack</strong>, I enjoy working with <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://nodejs.org/"
          target="_blank">Node.js</a
        >, <a class="font-bold" href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank">Next.js</a>, <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://www.honojs.com/"
          target="_blank">hono</a
        >,
        <a class="font-bold" href="https://expressjs.com/" target="_blank">express</a>, and express-like frameworks. I
        also have a decent understanding of <a class="font-bold" href="https://www.php.net/" target="_blank">PHP</a>, <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/"
          target="_blank">Ruby</a
        > (and <a class="font-bold" href="http://rubyonrails.org/" target="_blank">Rails</a>), and several <strong
          >SQL and NoSQL databases</strong
        >, such as <a class="font-bold" href="https://www.postgresql.org/" target="_blank">PostgreSQL</a>, <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://www.mysql.com/"
          target="_blank">MySQL</a
        >, <a class="font-bold" href="https://sqlite.org/" target="_blank">SQLite</a>, and <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://www.mongodb.com/"
          target="_blank">MongoDB</a
        >. Finally, I am a big fan of <a class="font-bold" href="https://www.linux.org/" target="_blank">Linux OS</a>
        (currently using <a class="font-bold" href="https://www.ubuntu.com" target="_blank">Ubuntu</a> and <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://get.opensuse.org/tumbleweed/"
          target="_blank">OpenSUSE Tumbleweed</a
        > distros), <a href="https://git-scm.com/" target="_blank">Git</a>, and <a
          href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agile_software_development"
          target="_blank">agile methodologies</a
        >, and I try to practice <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Test-driven_development" target="_blank"
          >Test-Driven Development (TDD)</a
        > as much as possible. If you would like to learn more <strong>about me</strong>, feel free to take a look at <a
          class="font-bold"
          href="https://public.tsevdos.me/john_tsevdos_cv.pdf"
          target="_blank">my CV</a
        >.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
